    "description": [
      "61 pages : 21 cm",
      "Sketch of Gunin phonology, morphology and syntax spoken by Kwini people of Kalumburu, includes two short texts and notes on relationship of Gunin to other Kimberley languages; brief histories of the missions at Kalumburu and Forrest River and decimation of population by disease and massacres; cultural notes on social organisation, conception and mortuary beliefs and Wandjina mythology",
      "\"Gunin is not to be confused with Gooniyandi (also sometimes spelt Gunian), which language is spoken four hundred kilometres ... to the south.\"--Page 5, footnote",
      "Includes bibliographical references (pages 58-61)"
    ],
